The paper focuses on the use of UAVs as a mobile edge computing platform, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm uses reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of user association and resource allocation involves optimizing the system performance, which can be considered as a control problem (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the energy consumption of the system, which is related to the design of efficient algorithms for distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which are relevant topics in information theory (cs.IT).
